
Overview of noun ounce

The noun ounce has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (4) ounce, troy ounce, apothecaries' ounce -- (a unit of apothecary weight equal to 480 grains or one twelfth of a pound)
2. ounce, oz. -- (a unit of weight equal to one sixteenth of a pound or 16 drams or 28.349 grams)
3. snow leopard, ounce, Panthera uncia -- (large feline of upland central Asia having long thick whitish fur)
